🔒 Encapsulation in Java

📘 Definition:
    Encapsulation means wrapping data (variables) and code (methods) together into a single unit (class) and restricting direct access to some of the object's components.

    Matlab:
        Variables ko private banate hain
        Access karne ke liye getter aur setter methods banate hain

🎯 Goal of Encapsulation:
    Data ko secure karna (outside se direct access na ho)
    Class ke through hi data read or modify ho
    Logic ko control kar sakte ho (jaise value check karna setter mein)

🧍‍♂️ Real Life Analogy:
    Socho ek ATM machine:
    Tum direct cash box ko touch nahi kar sakte (like private)
    Tum sirf buttons (interface – get/set) ke through kaam kar sakte ho
    Waise hi Java class mein private data hota hai, aur use access karne ke liye public methods use karte hain.